text: Norbert Gastell (14 October 1929 - 26 November 2015) was an Argentine-born German voice actor who mostly dubbed American television shows into the German language. He was known for dubbing Homer Simpson. Gastell was born in Buenos Aires. Gastell died in Munich, Germany from complications following a stroke, aged 86.Retrieved 3 December 2015. ==References== ==Other websites== * * Norbert Gastell at the Deutsche Synchronkartei Category:1929 births Category:2015 deaths Category:Deaths from stroke Category:German voice actors Category:Argentine actors Category:Actors from Buenos Aires
